# ── Git LFS policy ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Binary blobs (images, fonts, themes, videos, compiled binaries) are
# tracked via Git LFS so the working tree and clone size stay sane.
# See the "LFS / large binaries" section of README.md for rationale
# and migration instructions.
#
# This file declares what gets stored in LFS going forward. Existing
# commits already in the repository history are NOT migrated by this
# PR — that is a separate `git lfs migrate` step (see README).
#
# If you author new binary content under `assets/`, `dot-config/...`,
# or anywhere else, it WILL be routed to LFS automatically via the
# patterns below — no per-file changes needed.
#
# Source: see `git lfs track --help` for the wildcard syntax.

# ── Images ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.webp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.bmp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Video / audio (only mp4 is currently tracked, but be permissive) ──
*.mp4 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.webm filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mov filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.mp3 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.ogg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Fonts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.ttf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.otf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.woff filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.woff2 filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Themes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.qbtheme filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Compiled / prebuilt binaries ───────────────────────────────────────
# These are checked in as a convenience for users who don't want to
# build them — see `dot-config/programs/src/` for sources.
*.bin filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Compiled binaries shipped under dot-config/programs/bin/ — these have
# no extension, so we pattern-match by parent directory.
dot-config/programs/bin/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Cursor data (extension-less binary files) ──────────────────────────
# Hu Tao Xcursor theme — extension-less binary cursor data.
dot-local/share/icons/Hutao-Cursor/cursors/** filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# ── Non-LFS rules below this line ──────────────────────────────────────
# Anything not matched above is treated as text (the default).

# ── Legacy compatibility (binary attributes used before LFS was wired up) ──
# Pre-existing commit history has these as plain Git objects. The lines
# below keep `git status` honest for those files going forward.
*.mp4 binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
